\section{Transcript resolution}{

If \code{transcript_id} is \code{NULL}, the chosen transcript is, in order: the
first non-empty \code{MANE_SELECT} among table rows for \code{gene}; otherwise the
first \code{CANONICAL == "YES"} row; otherwise the transcript with the most
rows for that gene. The genome build is read from \code{NCBI_Build}.
}

\section{HGVSc parsing}{

The leading \code{c.} integer of \code{HGVSc} is the variant anchor: positive
integers map to CDS positions, \code{-N} maps to the 5' UTR (negative axis),
\verb{*N} maps to the 3' UTR (axis position \code{cds_len + N}). Strings with
\code{+K} or \code{-K} immediately after the leading anchor (splice / deep
intronic) are not plotted and counted under "splice"; anything else that
fails to parse is counted under "unparsed". The caption lists both
counts.
}

\section{Ensembl source}{

By default the function calls \verb{<host>/lookup/id/<ENST>?expand=1;utr=1}
on \code{rest.ensembl.org} (GRCh38) or \code{grch37.rest.ensembl.org} (GRCh37) and
caches the lean parsed structure as
\verb{<cache_dir>/genestruct_ensembl_<ENST>_<assembly>.rds}. The cache
directory follows the same resolution chain as \code{\link[=gvr_lollipop]{gvr_lollipop()}} (explicit
arg -> env \code{GVR_CACHE_DIR} -> option \code{germlinevaR.cache_dir} ->
\code{tools::R_user_dir("germlinevaR","cache")} -> \code{tempdir()}). Set
\code{gtf_path} to a Gencode/Ensembl GTF to skip REST entirely; this requires
suggesting \code{rtracklayer} or falls back to a tiny streaming parser.
}

